drag effectively starts, which of course includes both data and window

dragging scenarios. This change modify the relevant code to reflect this

entry.title: [TTFPassGen] Fix crash on PasswordGenerationControllerImpl::OnTouchToFillForGenerationDismissed
entry.content:
The crash happens because of the failing check

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/password_manager/android/password_generation_controller_impl.cc;l=373;drc=c177416839ec7a3fe2fe6e91a7e8e519248f96bd;bpv=0;bpt=1?q=password_generation_controller_im&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc.

The problem here is that the call touch_to_fill_generation_controller_.reset() in

PasswordGenerationControllerImpl::HideBottomSheetIfNeeded() causes

PasswordGenerationControllerImpl::OnTouchToFillForGenerationDismissed()

to be called. And because

PasswordGenerationControllerImpl::HideBottomSheetIfNeeded() resets the

TTF state to none before calling the reset, the check fails.

The solution provided in this CL prevents the reciprocate

OnTouchToFillForGenerationDismissed call.

entry.content:
In this CL, we remove the local policy provider from the list of

providers send to the PolicyServices and create a field for it

in each PolicyService. This way each policy service can switch

between test policies and official ones.



We also ensure that managed profiles cannot have the test policies

be bypassed by the policy test page.



It is still possible to apply browser level policies after restart,

in that case, managed profiles are still not affected, but browser

policies that affect it may have a different behavior. This has a

entry.title: Reland "Notify OffscreenCanvas of lost context after a GPU crash"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit ac3db87b1ba40f01151c1fdbc45959f362e0bda8



The call to NotifyGpuContextLost is now done from the offscreen

rendering context. The frame dispatcher is not touched until the

TryRestore event is triggered (also from the offscreen rendering

context) and it can be rebuilt. I could not reproduce the ASAN issue

locally, but it is passing the bots referenced in bug 1491175.



Original change's description:

> Notify OffscreenCanvas of lost context after a GPU crash

>

> In order for an OffscreenCanvas to recover from a lost context caused by

> a GPU crash, it has to be notified of it via NotifyGpuContextLost. This

> change adds a check before an existing ResourceProvider is returned from

> OffscreenCanvas, in order to call NotifyGpuContextLost if the GPU was

> being used and its context has been lost.

>

> A test has been added to check that the context is restored correctly

> when issuing new draw calls after the GPU crash.
